        <abstract> 
<p>Glad to hear that LJ will repeat his notes to Gilbert White’s [<hi rend="italic">Natural history of</hi>] <hi rend="italic">Selborne</hi> [1843] in a separate work.</p>  
<p>Critical of G. R. Gray’s attaching his own name to <hi rend="italic">Furnarius cunicularius</hi> [in <hi rend="italic">Birds</hi>, pp. 65–6]. Strickland’s nomenclature laws are needed to check egoism.</p> 
        </abstract>
